def: Proceeding; advancing.Because it is language, -- ergo, processive. Coleridge.
In the manner of a guest.
An active principle of Arnica montana. It is a bitter resin.

Existing only in contemplation of law; not capable of actualvisible seizin or possession; not being an object of sense;intangible; -- opposed to corporeal. Incorporeal hereditament. Seeunder Hereditament.
A plant whose flowers may be dried without losing their form orcolor, as the pearly everlasting (Anaphalis margaritacea), theimmortelle of the French, the cudweeds, etc.
Same as Toward, a., 2.He's towardly and will come on apace. Dryden.
One of the varieties of calcite, barite, and feldspar, whichemit a fetid odor on being struck; -- called also swinestone.
